Package: grub-efi-amd64-signed
Version: {{ VER }}
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Gabriel Guillou guillou.gabriel@gmail.com
Homepage: https://github.com/DaemonCores/debian-bootc
Section: admin
Priority: required
Description: GRUB2 EFI binary for amd64 with BLS support (Fedora rhboot build)
 Provides a GRUB2 EFI binary (grubx64.efi) compiled from the Fedora
 rhboot/grub2 fork at a pinned upstream commit. Includes the blscfg and
 blsuki modules required by ostree and bootc for Boot Loader Specification
 (BLS) kernel entry management, which the standard Debian GRUB package
 does not provide.
 .
 Note: this binary is NOT signed by a Microsoft-trusted Certificate
 Authority. Secure Boot must be disabled or the signing key enrolled
 manually through MOK (Machine Owner Key) before booting a system
 deployed with this image.
